I fell down all the time and everything lasted longer with me.
I could never skate or skate with the other kids and was often taunted at school because of my way of walking and running.
Rodgers said that at the age of 13, after several operations to relieve her Achilles tendon and stretch her feet, she saw her medical record when her doctor left the room and read that she was suffering from FA.
"I felt guilty because I had been curious, so I didn't tell anyone, but I went home, searched for the disease in the library, and wrote to the FA Society," she said.
When I received an answer, I was shocked and terribly panicked.
I thought I would be in a wheelchair at 18 and die at 25, and in between I would slowly lose all my skills.
I did it all by myself and planned my own funeral.
